{
  "stem": "33.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Eventually there was a room for people with scarlet fever, too.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Not while I was there at the hospital.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So some of these people might have also survived.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My-- it was pretty-- I was-- I was pretty ill, because at 18, I think, that-- it takes a lot out of you.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You're older than you should be when you have the measles.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And after the disease itself was over, I was running a high fever for weeks.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They didn't actually know why, because, of course, we didn't have x-ray machines or nothing to establish what the route of sickness was.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They suspected that it was some kind of a secondary infection.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It could have been pulmonary or they didn't know exactly.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But I was running a really high fever.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My cousin kept me working at this hospital as a nurse, a nurse's aid, whatever you want to call that.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Obviously the hospitals weren't filled with people who really needed medical attention, except for the couple of the epidemics.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They were just there for show.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So I suppose they never knew what organization might force its way to Auschwitz one day, and they could just shut up the gas chamber for a day and show them around the hospital.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The same way as the postcards, I assume.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I was working actually in a ward where the scarlet fever people were.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And it was a very, very mild epidemic.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So they were basically doing very well, all of them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They had very slight fever at the beginning, and then they were OK.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Our duties were to sweep the room, which at the beginning, I think, the spoiled little brat I was, I think I never had a broom in my hand before.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
